Title: Anti-de Sitter Supersymmetry

Authors: Bernard de Wit and Ivan Herger

Comments: Lectures presented by B. de Wit at the Winter School of Theoretical

Physics, Polanica, Poland, February 1999. 23 pp., LateX file, requirespackages latexsym, amsfonts, cl2emult.clsJournal-ref: Lect.Notes Phys. 541 (2000) 79-100

We give a pedagogical introduction to certain aspects of supersymmetric fieldtheories in anti-de Sitter space. Among them are the presence of masslike termsin massless wave equations, irreducible unitary representations and thephenomenon of multiplet shortening.